    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to an egg-laying mammalian order four species classified in two suborders, extant members are the duck-billed platypus and the two species of echidna. Probably split from the lineage leading to other mammals in the Mesozoic.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
